Hydrogen can be stored in the form of chemical compounds such as metal hydrides. During the formation of the metal hydride, hydrogen molecules are split and hydrogen atoms are inserted in spaces inside the metal lattice. Metals (M) react directly with hydrogen at a definite temperature and pressure according to the following reaction:4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
